LogFile.FinalText: In many homes, you will find a pet, and most people prefer a dog or a cat. So far, the soft puppy is ahead of the cute kitten in the race to be Denmark's most popular pet. While the loyalty of the dog accounts for its great popularity, the numerous cat owners love the independence of the cat. While the average cat owner finds dogs too dependent and filthy, many dog owners think of cats as lazy an without personality. Many pet owners choose a pet which reflects their own personality. When the big, strong man buys a big, strong dog, the dog's features enhance the owner's ego. In return, the feminine woman often prefers a beatiful and elegant cat. A dog and a cat will usually get along if they are familiar with each other. Often, the dog owner and the cat owner will disagree more than their pets.
